			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">It would be really useful if, whenever a test in the Scons test suite crashes, a stack backtrace is printed, assuming the crash happens in untrusted code.

I implemented this in a changeset that is not committable at the moment:
http://codereview.chromium.org/3462021/show

This is really useful for testing nacl-glibc.  Without this, it is very difficult to work out where nacl-glibc programs have crashed.

It would be good to get this functionality integrated somehow, because I keep having to update this change, which is a pain.

I expect we could use the sel_ldr debug stub (GDB remote serial protocol) for this, but it doesn't work on Linux at the moment.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-09-26T16:56:55.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-10-26T11:35:26.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Available</ns2:status><ns2:cc>
